dot((1,3));
dot((1,4));
dot((2,0));
dot((2,1));
dot((2,2));
dot((2,3));
dot((2,4));
dot((3,0));
dot((3,1));
dot((3,2));
dot((3,3));
dot((3,4));
dot((4,0));
dot((4,1));
dot((4,2));
dot((4,3));
dot((4,4));
draw((0,3)--(3,4)--(4,1)--(1,0)--cycle);
label("$A$",(3,4),N);
label("$B$",(4,1),E);
label("$C$",(1,0),S);
label("$D$",(0,3),W);
[/asy]

Note that when we say the grid is 5 by 5 we mean that each row and column contains 5 dots!

